&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locum Upper limb Consultant Orthopaedic Surgeon -&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed term 6 months contract&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is for a vibrant and progressive Trauma/Upper Limb Locum consultant to join a well-established Orthopaedic department and deliver high quality care to the local community&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Middlesex University Hospital (WMUH) is an acute NHS hospital in Isleworth, west London, operated by Chelsea and Westminster Hospital NHS Foundation Trust. It is a teaching hospital of Imperial College School of Medicine and a designated academic health science partner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some cross site work will be part of this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant should have the ability and willingness to provide clinical leadership skills. Ability to demonstrate experience and skills in Shoulder surgery as we as full GMC Registration and inclusion on the Specialist registrar are essential requirements for this post. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post is whole-time and offers 10 PAs with on-call commitment with internal cover.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Edward Ibrahim - Consultant, Service Director&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address- edward.ibrahim@chelwest.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
